{{Infobox Protected area | name = Great Arctic State Nature Reserve | alt_name = Большой Арктический государственный природный заповедник | iucn_category = Ia | photo = Ursus maritinus.jpg | photo_caption = The Great Arctic Nature Reserve is one of the largest wildernesses on earth | map = Russia | relief = 1 | map_alt = | map_caption = | map_width = | location =Russian Arctic, [[Krasnoyarsk Krai]] and [[Taymyrsky Dolgano-Nenetsky District]] | nearest_city = | coordinates = {{coords|75|30|N|92|36|E|region:RU|display=inline, title}} | area = 41,692 km<sup>2</sup> | established = 1993 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = }} The '''Great Arctic State Nature Reserve''' ({{lang-ru|Большой Арктический государственный природный заповедник}}) is a [[nature reserve]] in [[Krasnoyarsk Krai]], [[Russia]]. With an area of {{convert|41692|km2|sqmi|sp=us}}, it is the largest reserve of [[Russia]] and [[Eurasia]], as well as one of the largest in the world. ==History== The Great Arctic State Nature Reserve was founded on May 11, 1993 by Resolution No.431 of the Government of the [[Russian Federation]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bigarctic.ru/Eng/|title=General Information and history|publisher=Great Arctic Nature Reserve|accessdate=October 31, 2009|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071008044746/http://www.bigarctic.ru/Eng/|archivedate=October 8, 2007|df=}}</ref> The Nature Reserves in Russia are known as ''[[zapovednik]]s''. ==Sections== The Great Arctic State Nature Reserve is divided into nine sections: *[[Dikson Island|Dikson]] - [[Sibiryakov Island|Sibiryakov]] section. *The [[Kara Sea]] Islands section, with a surface of {{convert|4000|km2|sqmi|sp=us}}. It includes the [[Kirov Islands|Sergei Kirov Islands]], the [[Voronina Island]], the [[Izvestiy TSIK Islands]], the [[Arkticheskiy Institut Islands]], the [[Sverdrup Island (Kara Sea)|Sverdrup Island]], the [[Uedineniya Island]] and a number of smaller islands. This section represents rather fully the natural and biological diversity of Arctic Sea islands of the eastern part of the Kara Sea. *The Pyasino section. Includes the [[Pyasino Gulf]] and the [[Pyasina River]] basin. *The [[Middendorff Bay]] *The [[Nordenskiöld Archipelago]] *The '''Lower Taimyr''' section. Includes the basin of the [[Taimyr River]] (upper and lower), as well as [[Lake Taimyr]]. *The Chelyuskin Peninsula. Includes the northern end of the [[Taimyr Peninsula]] *The '''Northern Reserve''' (Североземельский). *The [[Yenisei Gulf#Islands|Brekhovsky Islands]] Natural Reserve
==Ecology== {{also|Russian Arctic National Park}} Many animals and plants are meant to thrive within the Great Arctic State Nature Reserve without human disturbance. Among the animals that are protected by this reserve, some of the most important are the [[polar bear]], the [[Arctic fox]], the [[snowy owl]], the [[reindeer]] and the [[Beluga (whale)|beluga]].<ref>[http://www.wild-russia.org/ Wild Russia]</ref>
