*''[[Nozhat ol-Gholub]]'' / ''Nuzhat ul-Qulub'' ({{lang|fa|{{nastaliq|نزهه القلوب|fa}}}}) (~"Diversions of the Heart") English transl. of geog. part by [[Guy Le Strange|Le Strange]]<ref>trans. Guy le Strange E.J.Gibb Memorial Series</ref><ref>Hamd Allah Mustawfi Qazwini, Nuzhat al-Qulub, ed. Guy Le Strange, The Geographical Part of the Nuzhat al-Qulub (Leiden-London, 1915-19</ref>
*''[[Zafarnamah (Mustawfi)|Zafar-Nameh]]'' ({{lang|fa|{{nastaliq|ظفرنامه|fa}}}})
*[[Tarikh-i guzida|''Tarikh e Gozideh'']] ({{lang|fa|{{nastaliq|تاريخ گزيده|fa}}}}).
His tomb at [[Qazvin (city)|Qazvin]]is surmounted by a turquoise blue conical dome. ==Linguistic Impact of Illkhanate Rule== In his History of Tabriz, Mustawfi writes that the people of Tabriz had spoken [[Pahalavi]] Persian before the arrival of the Mongols but that during Illkhanate rule they had adopted Adhari Turkish. He mentions further that the people of [[Maragha]], [[Zanjan Province|Zanjan]] and [[Ardabil]] had had their own Persian dialects.
==Persia== ''Verily God hath preferred amongst His creatures of the Arabs the Quraysh, and among the Persians the men of Fars : for which reason the people of this province . . . were known as ' the Best of the Persians.''<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=NxXoAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA17&lpg=PA17&dq=verily+god+hath+preferred+amongst+his+creatures+of+the+arabs+the+quraysh+and+amongst+the+persians+the+men+of+fars&source=bl&ots=FlNSi4pnQm&sig=Pc2DA2wh9WrPXq35K7UPaMVdDQM&hl=en&sa=X&ei=5DlYVfvBNoSHsAX0y4HABg&ved=0CB4Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=verily%20god%20hath%20preferred%20amongst%20his%20creatures%20of%20the%20arabs%20the%20quraysh%20and%20amongst%20the%20persians%20the%20men%20of%20fars&f=false Kashani-Sabet 2014], p. 17.</ref><ref>[http://www.thebaluch.com/documents/THE%20DIMINISHING.pdf FRAGILE FRONTIERS: THE DIMINISHING DOMAINS OF QAJAR IRAN]</ref>
