{{Other uses|Karagöl (disambiguation){{!}}Karagöl}} {{Infobox protected area | name = Karagöl-Sahara National Park | alt_name = ''Karagöl-Sahara Milli Parkı'' | iucn_category = | photo = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | photo_width = | map = Turkey | map_alt = | map_caption = | map_width = | relief = yes | label = Karagöl-Sahara NP | label_position = left | mark = | marker_size = | location = [[Şavşat]], [[Artvin Province]], Turkey | nearest_city = | coordinates = {{coords|41|13|N|42|27|E|region:TR|display=inline, title}} | area = {{convert|3251|ha|abbr=on}} | designation = | authorized = | created = | established = {{start date|1994|08|31}} | designated = | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_ref = | governing_body = [[Ministry of Forest and Water Management (Turkey)|Ministry of Forest and Water Management]] | administrator = | operator = | owner = | world_heritage_site = | website = {{URL|http://www.milliparklar.gov.tr/mp/karagolsahara/index.htm}} | child = | embedded = }}
'''Karagöl-Sahara National Park''' ({{lang-tr|Karagöl-Sahara Milli Parkı}}), established on August 31, 1994, is a [[national park]] in the [[Şavşat]] district of [[Artvin Province]], Turkey. It is located in the [[Black Sea Region]] and formed by two separate areas, namely Karagöl and Sahara plateau. Karagöl is located at {{convert|45|km|mi|abbr=on}} from [[Şavşat]], while Sahara plateau is {{convert|17|km|mi|abbr=on}} from the town.<ref name="t"/><ref name="tbt1"/><ref name="tbt2"/><ref name="mp"/>
The national park covers an area of {{convert|3251|ha|abbr=on}} at an average elevation of {{convert|1800|m|ft|abbr=on}} above mean sea level.<ref name="mp"/>
