{{Infobox military installation |name = Pointe aux Canons Battery |partof = |location = [[Saint Pierre Island]], [[Saint Pierre and Miquelon]] |image = Cannons that Defended the Harbour Against The English.JPG |caption = Cannons that defended the harbour against the English |map_type = |map_size = |map_caption = |type = [[Fort]] |coordinates = {{coord|46.775163566|-56.16833266|type:landmark|display=inline}} |code = |built = |builder = |materials = |height = |site_area = |used = |demolished = |condition = |ownership = |open_to_public = Yes |controlledby = |garrison = |current_commander = |commanders = |occupants = |battles = |events = |image2 = |caption2 = |website = }}
The '''Pointe aux Canons Battery''' was a fort on the island of [[Saint Pierre Island|Saint Pierre]] in [[Saint Pierre and Miquelon]] built by the [[France|French]] to defend the islands from British attacks in 1690-1713. The 6 cannon battery was [[Raid on Newfoundland|destroyed by the British]] in 1702.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=OHM1QewI1CcC&pg=PA566&lpg=PA566&dq=forts+in+St.+Pierre+and+miquelon&source=bl&ots=e1rWVrJ3kr&sig=_nITT5E_olDV_-nj4XrmlaucMEc&hl=en&ei=6qrSSe7II4iSMp_FjdsC&sa=X&oi=book_result&resnum=5&ct=result#PPA566,M1 ''A History of Newfoundland from the English, Colonial and Foreign Records''], D. W. Prowse, at Google Books</ref>
The old cannon battery was replaced in the 19th century to defend the islands during the [[Crimean War]].<ref>[http://www.st-pierre-et-miquelon.com/english/lieux.php Landmarks & Monuments] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100725233206/http://www.st-pierre-et-miquelon.com/english/lieux.php |date=2010-07-25 }} at Saint Pierre et Miquelon website</ref> The [[Pointe aux Canons Lighthouse]] is located near the old fort site.
Four cannons now sit in a park near the site of the old fort, but traces of fort have disappeared with the development of the town.
